      "side": 1,
      "message": "Line 35: Making every InfoBox focusable adds non-interactive static content to the tab order globally. That can make keyboard navigation noisy or confusing, because Tab should generally move between actionable controls while screen readers can still browse static text with reading/navigation commands. Prefer exposing the accessible name/description without `activeFocusOnTab`, or gate focusability behind an opt-in property for wizard pages that explicitly need it.\n```suggestion\n    property bool focusableInfo: false\n\n    Accessible.focusable: focusableInfo\n    activeFocusOnTab: focusableInfo\n```",
